This is expected since `Translations` is simply a collection property.

You can override `ApplyAbpConcepts` in your `DbContext` to mark the entity entry as modified:

```c#
protected override void ApplyAbpConcepts(EntityEntry entry, long? userId, EntityChangeReport changeReport)
{
    if (entry.State == EntityState.Unchanged &&
        entry.Collections.Any(c => c.IsModified && c.Metadata.Name == "Translations"))
    {
        entry.State = EntityState.Modified;
    }

    base.ApplyAbpConcepts(entry, userId, changeReport);
}
```

